-- Yen Climbs Against Dollar, Euro in Early Asia Trading
-- B y   K r i s t i n e   A q u i n o
-- 2012-04-03T00:01:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/yen-climbs-against-dollar-euro-in-early-asia-trading.html
The yen gained against the dollar
and euro in early Asia trading.  Japan ’s currency reached 81.56 per dollar, the strongest
since March 9, before trading at 81.59 at 8:59 a.m. in  Tokyo ,
0.6 percent stronger than yesterday’s close in  New York . The yen
added 0.5 percent to 108.83 against the euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
